Again, you're entire discussion concerns routing, not naming.
Sure, the differences you point out are important, but the name
resolution scheme handles them all by allowing a resolver to indicate
one host that handle all mail for particular domain or subdomain
or set of hosts.  If you want routing while delivering, you can acheive
it by just telling your resolvers to react that way.

